, sondern auch den in Hegels Denken verborgenen Begriff des Medialen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aImagination (Philosophy). 4aBild. 4aDeutsche Philosophiegeschichte. 4aErkenntnistheorie. 4aImagination. 4aKant. 4aKultur. 4aKunst. 4aMedialität. 4aMedien. 4aMedienphilosophie. 4aMedientheorie. 4aMedium. 4aPhantasie. 4aPhilosophie. 4aWissenschaft. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh  aArt.  aCulture.  aEpistemology.  aGerman History of Philosophy.  aImage.  aImagination.  aKant.  aMedia Philosophy.  aMedia Theory.  aMedia.  aMediality.  aMedium.  aPhilosophy.  aScience.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2023z9783111024950oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839469590?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839469590423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839469590/original  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-TGPb2023